eNCA's John Bailey reports on the theft of automatic weapons from a military base in Pretoria. PRETORIA - Twelve soldiers, accused of stealing high-grade automatic weapons have been denied bail. Nineteen R4-rifles were discovered missing from the Lyttleton military base in Pretoria on Monday. It's believed the theft was an inside job, which took place over several weeks. READ: R4 rifles stolen from SANDF military base On Friday, four officers and eight non-commissioned officers appeared in a military court on charges of theft, house-breaking and loss of arms. The soldiers' lawyer, Brian Plaatjies, says their constitutional rights were denied while they were in custody. "There's no direct evidence presented that any of these accused have either been found in possession of the firearms, any direct evidence that someone saw them with the weapons.."